        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">String</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean.CoreM</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Unit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">throwErrorAt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HUH</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"bp\">!</span><span class=\"s2\">\"{x}\"</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean.CoreM</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Unit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">do</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">throwErrorAt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xxx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm not sure if this is a bug, but I found it surprising that <code>HUH</code> here becomes an implicit argument of <code>foo</code>, rather than this giving an error message  like <code>unknown identifier 'HUH'</code>, which is what happens for <code>xxx</code>.</p>",
